  :'en.insured.consumer_roles.search.enter_personal_info_msg' => "First, we need to verify whether you're new to %{site_short_name} or affiliated with another account. Please enter your personal information. When you're finished, select CONTINUE.",
  :'en.insured.consumer_roles.ridp_agreement.heading' => "Authorization & Consent",
  :'en.insured.consumer_roles.ridp_agreement.instruction1' => "Read the authorization and consent statement. You must select 'I Agree' to complete your application online. When you're finished, select Continue to Next Step.",
  :'en.insured.consumer_roles.ridp_agreement.instruction2' => "For your security, we need to verify your identity before you can proceed. If you agree, you are providing consent to Experian to access your personal information to conduct identity verification on behalf of the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS) — part of the US Department of Health and Human Services (HHS). Below are a few items to keep in mind.",
  :'en.insured.consumer_roles.ridp_agreement.bullet1' => "Make sure that you entered your legal name, current home address, phone number, date of birth and email address correctly. We will only collect personal information to verify your identity with Experian, a third party identity verification provider.",
  :'en.insured.consumer_roles.ridp_agreement.bullet2' => "To verify your identity, Experian uses information from your consumer credit report profile. As a result, you may see an entry called a “soft inquiry” on your Experian consumer report. Soft inquiries are only visible to you, are never shared with third parties, and do not affect your credit score. The soft inquiry will be titled “CMS Proofing Services” and will be removed from your Experian consumer report after 25 months.",
